HEADWORD: Livraison
<hw>Li`vrai`son"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. L.
<ets>liberatio</ets> a setting free, in LL., a delivering up. See
<er>Liberation</er>.]</ety> <def>A part of a book or literary
composition printed and delivered by itself; a number; a part.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

